    <note>Zhai(2) Ruwen [8128] His ancestors moved to Suzhou, Changshu xian, possibly when his great grandfather, Tao [3841], was magistrate of Changzhou xian. However, other evidence would suggest that Ruwen was the person who moved and since there are no Zhai(2)'s in the Suzhou degree lists, other relatives (with exception of eldest son, Qinian [10216], who is also listed as a temporary resident of Suzhou) must have remained in Danyang. Xing(1) Shu's [7106] son-in-law. Zhai Ruwen, WJ, 'fu,' 1.1a; State council. Qinian was the only  son of Xing(1) Shu's daughter, Two other sons, 8 grandsons, and 4 great grandsons listed. [ADD]. CBD, 4, 3312-3313.</note>
